	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 257-63" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8662> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8662" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 745, footnote 222" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7182> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7182" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Tr. pl. 120, Pr. 115. Badian holds that he was a son of P. Decius Subolo (20), who bore the cognomen himself (Liv. Oxy. Per. 48; Cic. De Or. 2.253 and 277; Val. Max. 6.1.10), and was prominent with Marius in the post-Gracchan period (JRS 46, 1956, 91-96). In his praetorship the consul Aemilius Scaurus had his clothing torn, his curule chair broken, and forbade his judicial activity (Auct. Vir. Ill. 72.6). On his prosecution of Opimius, see Gruen, RPCC 102-105, and on the attack on him, 109-111. On his career and connections, see Badian, op. cit., and comments in Scullard, From the Gracchi to Nero 393.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3378> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3378" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Because of his refusal to rise out of respect, the Consul Scaurus tore his vestments, broke his official chair, and ordered that none should bring cases to him (Auct. Vir. Ill. 72.6)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3326> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3326" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Prosecuted Opimius for punishing Roman citizens uncondemned, but failed to convict him (see Consuls, on Carbo; Cic. De Or. 2.132-135, 165, 169; Liv. Per. 61; cf. Cic. De Or. 2.106; Brut. 103, and 128; Part. Or. 104, and 106)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3325> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3325" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In Liv. Per. 61 the praenomen is Q., but the evidence of Cicero (Brut. 108) and Auct. Vir. Ill. (72.6) favors P." .
